caption: I absolutely love this place. I've been here on numerous occasions and the staff is always a delight. The service is quick (I've ordered calling ahead and as a walk-in) and I've never waited too long. I've had the following from their menu:  Burrito - Crunch&Fire Burrito - Soft Shell Crab Bulgogi Fries - Bulgoki  I highly recommend the crunch and fire anything, it's DELICIOUSNESS!

I had the spicy tuna poke bowl and the tempura shrimp sushi taco. I loved the poke bowl! The sushi taco was a bit weird. The tempura shrimp sat on top of it, so you couldn't really eat it easily. I had fun with it all though and will certainly be coming back.
Have had the sushi burritos and tacos. They're good portions and tasty.
Their sushi burritos are so good! And they are pretty big

This place is extremely rude and does not give refunds for their own mistakes. Called me a liar for a specific order I made because of my debilitating disease and requested a picture and still did not show any sympathy upon presenting them their mistake for an error they made. Never going to come here again.

Got some Poké and Sushi Tacos 😧‼️ First of all I didn’t know there was such thing as that LOL; I found this place because I was craving Poke and I’m very happy I found this place because I got introduced to my new favorite thing: SUSHI TACOS!  I ordered a Shrimp Tempora Taco and Taco Fire both w/o rice  🔥 And I went with the Crunch&Fire Poke bowl  Overall think it was worth the price for the portion size of the bowl - and there are a lot more things on the menu that I neeed to try! I’ll be back 🙌🏽

Even in the pandemic they are thriving and don’t skimp on the flavor and the portions.  I seriously love this place. The dishes are sooooo good for the price. I like to get the Spicy Salmon/Tuna bowl and then get shrimp tempura on the side to add to the bowl lol. And the Kimchi fries are perfection, I usually get enough to have some leftover the next day for reheating. Try this place you will love it if you like Poke and spicy food. Even if it’s not a spicy meal, the flavor explodes from the dish.  It’s fantastic!
Crunch poke bowl is unreal! Great fresh ingredients that go together so well and large portions. Love the burritos and the poke bowls.

This has been the best delivery/era-of-covid find!! We can’t believe it’s been so close to us, yet we’ve never had it before. Absolutely delicious and everything tastes so fresh! Could not recommend more!

I ordered the Shoyu Ahi Tuna Poke Bowl with both mayo sauces on the side. I am glad I got the sauce on the side, because the onion maple mayo tastes exactly like ranch dressing and would have ruined everything. The rest of the dish made no sense to me and seemed like a bunch of random leftover ingredients thrown together. Marinated (was it actually?) tuna is flavorless and scarce. The greens have more flavor, and the beet greens in particular overpower the tuna. The rice and sweet potato were really warm and felt gross combined with the rest of the f cold ingredients: half cooked carrots, cucumber, pickled? radish, edamame, and a lime wedge. Please revisit this recipe because limes, sweet potato, and ranch dressing are a horrible combination of flavors.
Shrimp tempura poke bowl was delicious and filling
Absolutely amazing. Try the kimchi fries
Great breakfast burrito
Love En Hakkore so much! Had great experiences with both dine-in and carry out. Their sushi burritos are the BEST and are only $12! This is my go-to place whenever I’m in the mood for sushi
Delicious, fresh food at a reasonable price. I highly recommend the Savory Bowl and the Unagi Lover Burrito!
Fresh raw fish (sushi burrito & poke) and helpful staff members who make sure you get quality food!
High quality, fresh ingredients! Everything is so delicious!! The kimchi fries are a must. You won't be disappointed!!
I ordered a crunch burrito and 2 tacos  savory and shrimp tempura. Everything was great. I had to re order since everyone at home couldn't stop eating my food lol.
Interesting menu, delicious although unconventional!

The first time I ate here, I became a fan of sushi burritos. The second time I ate here, I was converted into a bowl fan. Either way, you can't go wrong! Had great experiences with both dine-in and delivery.  The fish is fresh and the sauces are flavorful. There's a variety of toppings to add to the bowl for extra texture and flavor (the sweet potato was my favorite). For salmon lovers, the salmon wafu bowl and the friend burrito are the ways to go. The portions for the bowl are bigger than the burritos.

We've ordered from here a handful of times since March, and for good reason. The sushi burritos are huge, are stuffed full of yummy fillings, and are ONLY $12! That's cheaper than a regular sushi roll anywhere. Bulgogi fries are also tasty with the sauces they come with. They get kind of soggy with delivery but it really doesn't matter. The poke bowls are also so large but just a tad too saucy. Overall, such a great place to do takeout from and the value is unbeatable!

Wow, I’m been ordering from the other location since they opened. I decided to order from this location and now I have two great fusion Korean places by me for to go / delivery.  I ordered the Crunch & Fire Burritos w Kimchee fries - did not expect the texture and taste of what I received. Like a giant crispy rice sushi roll! The fries...I just had to add ketchup and then I was in some kind of Korean fast food taste heaven! I know I’m sounding a bit fanboyish, but yes, I liked it!
I work close by and am vegitarian. I love their vegitarian options 🌮🍲🍚
Really great. Everything is good. Love the poke and LOVE bulgogi kimchi fries. Fast service.

AMAZING!!! This place is my absolute favourite in the area. Fresh, quick, well priced and always super tasty. You really can’t go wrong with any of the menu items. My personal favourite is the Friend sushi burrito. The bulgogi fries are a great side and the tacos are a bit more pricy for the amount of food but so worth it!!
Yummy!
Tried this place for the first time yesterday and I’m on my way back today! Seriously that good! Recommend fire and crunch burrito and ahi tuna tacos❤️👏
Amazing veggie burrito!
I got the Crunch sushi burrito and it was amazing. I’ll be coming to this location again.
These poke bowls are so delicious and filled with fresh veggies. I love that you can get spring mix added with the rice.
This place is pretty good. I've never actually ate in because I always order out. This is the place I order from when I'm too lazy to cook. I usually get a crunch. Not bad.
Love the original En Hakkore and 2.0 did not disappoint! Fresh, vibrant poke bowls filled with tasty nutrients 😋
We ordered the Savory Poke Bowl for takeout. The portions were large and the food was delicious!
This is my favorite poke bowl place in the city! I order takeout regularly and it’s consistently delicious and fast and easy.
Amazing and delicious poké bowl and Kimchi fries! Ordered through UberEats and had a great delivery experience. Definitely ordering from them again.
Nice place. The lunch special of pad Thai was a touch too sweet for my taste. Thai ice tea was good. The free ice cream to end my meal was a really nice touch on a hot day.
Soy garlic chicken is good. My only complaint is why doesn't it come with rice? It used to and the chicken is expensive. Rice should be a side option.

Excellent quick meals. The poke bowls have fresh ingredients.  The burritos have lightly toasted rice on the outside, yum!  Kim chi fries are a fun snack!  Place your order and prepay.  They’ll bring your food order to the table.   Self seating and self service for cups of water, plastic utensils and sauces of your choice!  Tip is optional. Tables and booth style seating.  Everything is delicious and fresh.

Excellent quick meals. The poke bowls have fresh ingredients.  The burritos have lightly toasted rice on the outside, yum!  Kim chi fries are a fun snack!  Place your order and prepay.  They’ll bring your food order to the table.   Self seating and self service for cups of water, plastic utensils and sauces of your choice!  Tip is optional. Tables and booth style seating.  Everything is delicious and fresh.
Loved the bibimbap burrito and the Spiderman soft shell crab.
My absolute favorite poke bowls

We love to order from here. They have delicious sushi burritos. Our favorites are the fire, crunch and friend burritos. I feel like they are reasonably priced. Sometimes I can split the burrito into 2 meals depending on how hungry I am. I recommend trying it out and don’t think you’ll be disappointed!
This place offers fantastic service as well as yummy meals. The best place ever. The food arrived fast and the prices are inexpensive. I recommend this place.
Excellent spot, good bowls and solid sides
Tasty sushi burritos in low key atmosphere.
So very very good. Bulkogi burrito is fantastic as well as everything in my party was highly rated.
Ahi Tuna and Salmon poke bowl was excellent. Will definitely be back!
Cute, counter service and very fresh tasting. Never seen the taco concept before. Chill vibe. Tasty!

Really great place for poke, or better yet, poke tacos! The tacos come in a crispy seaweed shell and are stuffed with fish or whatever toppings you get in them. There are several different options. They are delicious, but kind of pricey. The sushi burritos are usually good, but sometimes have too much rice. There are many seats. This is a great casual spot for a quick meal or takeout!
Exceptional good food. Exotic drinks. This restaurant is worth a trip from everywhere.  Neat and clean.

The interior of the restaurant provides a perfect mood for a date! The foods can be little pricey but is definitely worth it. (their shrimps are soooo good) Service and the staff members are really nice. I definitely recommend you guys to try it out!

Compared to other Poke places, I have to say En Hakkore's sushi seems a lot fresher and its portion is generous.  My favorite is Fire Tuna bowl,  all these fresh ingredients come in one good looking bowl, love the taste. Also, highly recommend crunch suchi taco, amazingly crunchy and flavorful. One of my best go to spots in Chicago.
One Of Best spot in Wicker . Food is Amazing and customer Service is Top notch .. only thing bad is they closed on Sunday....

EN HAKKORE CHANGED MY LIFE. My life can be divided into two parts; before sushi burrito and after sushi burrito. I will refer to these periods as B.S. and A.S. The bulgogi fries were DIVINE. The sushi burritos were massive and packed with delicious seafood goodness. It is might tasty.

caption: Long time visiter of the OG En Hakkore and have been to this location a few times now. Everything is delicious and the prices are fair considering the location. Nearly everything on Milwaukee Ave is twice as expensive for half the amount of food.  For instance the "mini beef bowl" is more like the mighty beef bowl! The soft shell crab taco is chock-full with an entire crab hanging out the top.  You pay at the front register. So, no worries about splitting checks. Lastly, the service is snappy which is great for lunch visits.

Delicious poke bowls, sushi burritos, and more! It’s always really fresh when I’ve been and it’s just delicious food! Highly suggest the poke bowls. Also, it’s really nice environment inside even though it’s order-at-the desk
Great food if you like Vietnamese food.
good food and good value.  Fast.
(Translated by Google) good to eat  (Original) 好吃
First time here. Fire tuna bowl with black rice... wow so good and flavorful. If you also like spicy this def is the one for you. Repeat customer for sure.

We ordered two starters first one was the salmon rolls they were so good and scallop it was amazing. We got two entrees wasabi noodles and sea bass. I gave this place 4 stars for two reasons: the tables are so small they barely could fit two plates next to each other. The second reason is the steak was average.
My new favorite place, the food is amazing if you like Poke bowls and fresh fish
Super cute and super delicious place. The price is reasonable for how much for you get too.

Their sushi burrito is definitely better than the poke bowls. They pack the same things for both, and for sushi burrito, the flavor was great but not overwhelming. But having it spread out into a bowl, it became rather bland and harder to eat while trying to mix things together. The karaage ones are also pretty great!
The fries looked nice, but could have been a bit warmer.
Great price, fast service, very clean, incredibly tasty.
Fantastic food. Highly recommended for anyone who likes sushi and sashimi
Food was great. But customer service at the counter was extremely poor. Very rude girl.

Wow. This place has been on my “wanted to go” list since they opened and I finally got to check it out. The boy and I decided to split a burrito and a bowl and share some bugolgi fries. Everything was incredible. Still not entirely sure about the burrito, I love the ability to mix all the ingredients in the bowl, whereas with the burrito you risk taking a bite that’s entirely jalapeño. Good portion size for the price. Will definitely be back as I didn’t even know they had tacos!!
My mind is blown. The food here is incredible!!! Everything on the menu is insane and worth at least trying once.

Super fresh veggies and really tasty preparations. Great value in a bright dining space. I feel downright virtuous eating such healthy food despite it being delicious. I'm typically a traditionalist, but the pork is even better than the beef imho.

Don't miss out on this place! Ingredients are very fresh. The seasonings and sauces are incredible. Great prices for what you're getting. It's so fresh I suspect they have an aquarium and a garden in back! If you get a burrito or poke bowl, make sure you grab a sauce bottle of their hot sauce from the back (the unmarked one, not the Sriracha). In my top three of Wicker Park spots.
The Savory poke bowl was delicious! I'd definitely recommend it if you are into a healthy and satisfying meal :)
Perfect poke bowl!
I loved their poke bowl called fire tuna! A big sized portion and soooo yummy. Also their kimchi fries are fire. Definitely will come back.
Best Food Ever!
En Hakkore Sushi Burrito & Poke Bowl is the new up coming hotpot place to be! Jay our waiter hooked us up and you cant beat the all you can eat. Really good decor and amazing food. Check it out!
My favorite comfort food ...their kimchi fries!!!
Delicious bowls - they taste just as good as they look. Place is clean, friendly, quick service. A great address for a healthy tasty meal full of flavor.
Some of the best poke in the city and their kimchi fries are great too! Almost as good as del Seoul. Love this place so much. Their sushi burritos are also bomb too
Delicious! And very good location!
Yo, just go.
Yum yum yum! The sushi burritos and poke bowls are amazing here! Very affordable and fast. My go to place for a quick, delish and healthy meal!
Delicious food and generous portion sizes. High-five for the gender-inclusive restrooms!
Good food

Nice casual spot, very clean and cozy and ambiance is modern. Great friendly service and the foot is awesome. Best looking poke bowls I've ever seen. Sushi tacos are so cool. Had savory suchi taco with a shell that just melts in your mouth and very fresh seafood. Will definitely return!  Update: I keep coming back over and over and this place is consistently great. Savory sushi taco is my favorite. The fish is fresh, sauce delicious, and the seaweed taco shell melts in your mouth. Service is always prompt and friendly.
Best shrimp tempura taco with crunchy seaweed shell. Blew my mind!
Amazing fusion food, get the bulgoki fries!
Fresh fish, decently quick service, a good amount of different menu items. Cute little place!
Would be better if they hadn't discontinue their sizzling BBQ pork bowl

Awesome, awesome combination of South Asian dishes all in one bowl! Or taco. Or lettuce wrapped taco! Their Lychee Tea is a must!! So is their bread with Jam! All their ingredients taste wholesome and fresh. Definitely plan on trying the rest of their menu. Ordering is Chipotle-style, made to order!

I like how good it tastes for being so healthy. Bowl or tacos. Interesting combos for meatballs with salad type ingredients. In form of a taco or bowl style. Comes with 3 tacos or a very decent size bowl.  I was shocked the price wasn't more for non-GMO organic food.

Tried this on a whim as a quick healthier meal, it definitely exceeded my expectations. I got the green tea noodles with all the veggies and it was amazing! Enough food that I was able to split it into two meals. The staff was extremely friendly and helpful!

This was my second favorite spot for poke after the demise of FireFin.  It's a bit more expensive, but they give the same amount of fish that you expect and a ton of different vegetables.  I also love that they have black/purple rice and give you a 50/50 mixture of rice and salad.  If that sounds like your style, then know that I like this better than aloha poke.
Had the salmon kimchi poke bowl and horchata. Great portions and flavor. Laid back atmosphere.
This place Gave me the very worst food poisoning ever. Very very disturbing experience.

Always loved this place and now they added poké bowl. Everything tastes good and they are very fast. There's nothing not to like about this place. It's too bad that they don't have a bar even though it looks like they planned for one.
Good food at a great price
Decent prices and very filling sushi burrito
The food was pricy but good. Losing one star for not their fault but there was no parking. Instead of sit down, we had to carry out.
Love the sushi tacos here. I ordered the savory sushi taco plenty of times and it's always on point. The bulgogi fries are also good.
Amazing bowls!
The service was super friendly, the portions were generous, and the food tasted great! So hard to choose, they all sounded good!

Ordered the fire tuna poke bowl, friend sushi burrito and fries with kimchi and bulgoki; very good quality and priced well. Decent selection of non-alcoholic drinks. The establishment was clean and simply decorated. Service was polite.
Omg This place wad phenomenal! Must try everything.  My first time eating a poke/ sushi taco, i could eat 10 of these, that's how good they were!
Ignore all other sushi burrito places this is the only one to go. It is such a tough decision to go taco or burrito. The fries are something else as well.
Deliciois sushi burritos!!
Delicious innovative poke dishes! Loved the salmon taco.
Whoa, didn't know good poke existed in Chicago....fast, friendly and casual service. Order at counter and they drop it off at your table...had the fire poke bowl...so good!

Crunch + Fire Burrito...i was so excited until I finally tried it!  The tuna was slimy and not edible...it ruined my burrito!  The sauce was bleeding down on the bottom of the burrito which means it wasn't evenly distributed on the burrito. The ingredients in this burrito should be winners hands down but the flavors were off. They didn't execute today and for a small Burrito $12 is overpriced.  Also, not impressed with the after taste which to me means nothing was as fresh as it should be.  The ambiance was pretentious and no one was friendly.  Felt a bit mislead by the great reviews but you never know until you try it for yourself.  So wouldn't go back or recommend it to anyone.  Way better options out there and I'm willing to pay more for quality and consistency.
Just go. Tacos are amazing
Sushi burritos are amazing!
Love the crunchy sushi burrito!! I taken multiple people there and they absolutely love it as much as I do! Also, the service is fast! 👍🏼
Just YUM! Hit the spot and superb service

This was a fantastic Asian fusion restaurant that exceeded my expectations. I have a salmon pokey bowl, and it was absolutely fantastic. Nothing negative to comment about. I’ll definitely come here again.
Poke bowl was fabulous. Atmosphere was chill, despite a busy restaurant.
Love this place.

Crunch/fire combo burrito (Spicy tuna + shrimp tempura) is my go to burrito here everytime!  This is truly a unique taste experience in Chicago that everybody should experience! I can’t go without a month without craving the need to indulge in this gastronomic delight. (and such a value for amount of food per price.)
The best poke place in the city! Everything is very fresh and service is great. Highly recommend.
Slightly pricey for the area  but the food is both very original and of high quality.

So worth your time. We had the sushi taco with eel, a sushi burrito, and a poke bowl. All were amazing. The ingredients are fresh, the flavors are outstanding. Even my pickiest eater in tow loved it. Staff was friendly and helpful. Cucumber water is available and tasty, but they also had a nice assortment of beverages, including "Asian horchata" which was a green tea sort of thing that was actually quite refreshing
We had a spicy burrito and a savory bowl. Both we're excellent.

Best sushi burrito and poke bowl in town! It’s packed with nutritious ingredients. I’ve cheated on them a few times and I regretted that. Posting up pic to make up for my wrongdoing. :) please don’t go anywhere! I hope their business will flourish!
Simple, fresh, tasty, affordable. It was a treat.
Quick, delicious, fresh, affordable, hits the spot! I wish I knew about this place sooner.
Good food, great price
Good qualities and good price! The bowls are super authentic and fresh. Best poke in the are by far!

Interesting combinations of Sushi, Korean, Border standards. The kimchi fries have a nice spicy kick and don't require any other condiment. Softshell Crab and Spicy Tuna (among others) can be had in the taco and burritos. No booze served but dining in can be paired with interesting people watching on busy Milwaukee Ave.
Excellent tacos, fries and bowl. Crunchy and delicious!
Delicious and reasonably priced!
Best sushi burritos on the planet. 🖤
One of my favorite quick spots in the city
People were super friendly and the food was amazing. Had fire and crunch sushi burrito and kimchi fries. No regrets.

These were the freshest and tastiest sushi burritos I've ever had. It took a while for the burritos to come out, but you can tell that they were made to order as they came out nice and warm. My family ordered several different ones, and we all enjoyed them very much! I'll definitely be coming back.
Fresh food, kind staff, great atmosphere. You’d be stupid not to go here. My fave is the Fire Crunch Sushi Burrito.
Exquisite
Delicious sushi burritos and poke bowls, decent service

We accidentally stumbled upon this place and what a gem!Non pretentious,tasty and super fresh.  Poke bowl was amazing and I highly recommend the soft shell crab sushi burrito as well.Will be returning again and again.

The restaurant is a little hard to see as a big tree is blocking the sign. Overall it is a nice restaurant for a quick bite. Prices are reasonable. Portion sizes were good. Food looked delicious and was tasty. The menu has a variety of pokebowls and sushi burritos that you can choose from as well as appetizers.   It is a casual environment. Nice ambiance. I'd say its a great place to meet your friends for a meal/ date night. Staff was super friendly and nice.
Kimchi is fantastic. My wife has the spicy tuna bowl which she loved and I had a vegetarian bowl. Reasonable price and Highly recommended
Sushi tacos...need I say more. So good! Dream about these tacos- highly recommend.

Innovative sushi tacos and burritos. The tacos are tempura fried seaweed fitted with sushi, vegetables and sauce. I had the savory and eel tacos. Both very tasty and the fish very fresh. The service was super fast and the staff very friendly. Seating is either at the bar, booths, or tables. The window front can be opened to give the feeling of seating outside.
The bee's knees when it comes to sushi burritos
Used to be excellent.  They got rid of multiple menu options and their quality seems to have decreased.  Imitation crab meat as an example.

only went here because firefin closed. blandest poke ive ever had. threw most of it away. they also messed up my order and gave me salad instead of rice and by the time i walked home it was too late to do anything about it. wouldnt go back even if it was free.
Love this place, feels like a better bang for your buck when you’re craving sushi.
We have come here many times, and consistently get the burritos and tacos.  The fish is always very fresh, and the burritos are massive.    Overall, try one of the sides of fries.. Theyre killer.
Delicious and great value. Kimchi fries very crispy. Bulgogi bowl. Very meaty Sushi-rito! Friendly staff!
From the black rice poke bowls to the soft shell crab taco- this place is delicious every time.
The sushi tacos are amazing.

Their bulgogi fries are super tasty and so nicely done. The sauce, the garnish, the seasoning on the fries, the tenderness of the meat... yum! Their sushi burritos are a nice size. The sauce in the Fire sushi burrito is really delicious. And the Fire spicy level delivered on its description, too! I shared an appetizer and sushi burrito with a friend and it was enough food. Service is quick and simple. I’d love to come back here for dine-in and to-go! Maybe tonight?
Super creative. Best combination of 3 different cuisines: Japan, Korean, Mexican.
You guys have outdone yourselves.  I’m literally rolling around in bed just thinking about what just went down.  Got a fire crunch burrito with kimchi fries.  My God.
Best sushi burrito and poke in wicker park!

The vegetarian burrito is fresh and the tofu is really texturally nice.  Great miso soup and the kimchi fries were perfectly spicy.  Love the fusion concept, works really well.  The iced korean horchata is a percect example of that.

The food is always delicious! Bimbimbop and tacos are the best!

Food was so so good. Their veggies are fresh. Tacos seaweed was so good! You should come and try it.
Great service and great refreshing food.

Pretty good sushi burritos and fried chicken at affordable prices

VERY DISSATISFIED WITH the quality and service would realy liked to give them stars but thought they could have done better especially with the food sorry will never be going back good luck cheating your customers

They have sushi burritos, and they're quite amazing. Good variety on the menu here, veggies and fish were fresh and tasty.  Very reasonably priced too as for a mere $10-13 you're getting a huge amount of food which is a noticably larger amount of sushi goodness when compared to say ordering a specialty roll at a normal sushi joint. They also carry a few other items such as noodle bowls of similar composition and of course sushi tacos.

Anytime I'm in wicker park I try to come here. Burritos are delicious

Delicious  try the tacos!  Wish i lived closer !

Wonderful food here. My only complaint is that their menu seems to change randomly, and they don't update their menus anywhere.  Examples:  last month I tried to phone an order into them based on their website menu. Three of the things I wanted to order "no longer exist". I came by a week later in person and ordered off their printed paper menu at the register -- once again I was told that the the item I wanted to order was no longer made, and would I like to order this other similar thing instead?  I came back a month after that and the *same* experience happened with a *different* printed menu item!  TL;DR:  just reprint your menus and update your website. It's not that hard. :-)

Very open and unique place. Everything on the menu is pretty good. If you're in a burrito mood get the sushi burrito, but if you want to switch it up the poke and bulgogi bowls are excellent. In all honesty as I was eating my burrito the first time I looked over in envy at another person's bulgogi bowl. This caused me to come back the following week to get it and I was not disappointed.
The sushi tacos are amazing. Crispy seaweed shells are inspired. I'm hungry to return for more.
Staff was friendly. Food came fast and fresh.
Amazing.  Visiting from Boston, really wish Boston had a place like this.  We tried the poke bowl and tacos, and loved both.  The taco shell made of seaweed is amazing!
Everything here is delicious. It quickly became my favorite restaurant in the area. The wings are big and flavorful. The crunch +fire burrito is the bomb. Great poke bowls as well.
Great sushi burrito and fries
The burrito sushi was delish! Great attentive service.
Bulgogi burrito was good, would love if they brought over the bi bim bap from the original location.

Everyone raves about the bbq beef, but that was over-rated (heavy oil, not so much flavor). The food is all right, though, and the hours are good, plus their prices are fair. (I guess having a Korean step-mom may have spoiled me?) If you're staying at the Hollander/Robey, go across the main intersection and up Damen.

Awesome sushi burritos. I never knew this was a thing until I came here, and now (and everyone else I brought here) is obsessed. The best is the soft shell crab one. Also the poke salad is amazing. It's a good place to eat, talk, and relax. It's counter-order and they bring the food to you. No alcohol and not BYOB either.
This was a great experience for a quick lunch. Get the peach drink!

They added more poke bowl menu items that capitalize on this noteworthy food trend. I ordered the savory version and both the tuna and salmon were super fresh. One small hitch that reduces the stars from 5 to 4: maple syrup mayo adds too much sweetness to what really should be a savory dish. Next time I'll order it sans the maple mayo.
Quick service and amazing food! A unique take on classic sushi flavors. Has a cozy and low-key interior make it great for lunch. Inexpensive, and fantastic tea as well!

My wife and I love this place, it's one of our favorite spots in Wicker Park. We've always gotten their sushi burritos, but they recently revamped their menu with some new offerings. So far we've had the pork belly and a poke bowl, both of which were amazing. The pork belly in particular was a good balance of being super rich and flavorful without being too heavy. It came with a sauce that was almost like a thicker ramen broth - it was so good that I think I'd be happy just eating that sauce over rice.  Good prices, awesome food, quick service, friendly staff - last time we went, the guy up front was clearly pumped for us to try the new food. If you want to go to a sit-down place with fast, solid food, I can't recommend this spot enough.

(Translated by Google) Fully recommended chicken with honey-related sauce !!! Tteokbokki and gimbap are just normal? Chicken is awesome !!!  (Original) 허니관련 소스로 된 치킨 완전 강추!!! 떡복이랑 김밥은 그냥 보통? 치킨은 대박입니다!!!
Interesting Korean fusion food. Wasn't happy with the Kimchi fries, they were like hash browns, too oily and too little Kimchi but lots of mayonnaise.

Literally one of my favorite place - I never tried sushi burrito 🌯 but after trying one, now I can't forget about it. Even the name itself sounds amazing; it's sushi and burrito - what can go wrong? The burrito is pretty big so it will fill up your system and I recommend getting either Crunch or Fire, and chicken wings (I think the honey chicken or maybe garlic was amazing).

This is great casual place if you aren't in the mood for the ordeal of a typical sit down. You order at the front and seat yourself. The food is good, the service is fast, and the prices are reasonable. Sushi burritos don't get old, at least for me. The skillet is also huge, even I had trouble finishing it, which is uncommon. Love it
Yummy food, fast and friendly service.  Hip, but not pretentious.  Can't wait to return!
Too long waiting time

I went with family and was able to try a little bit of everything. The kimchi fries where fantastic, the sushi burritos where tasty and a great portion, and then Pork Bulgogi Sizzling Pan was the right amount of spicy. I would highly recommend it and go here again!
I love the kimbap here and the sushi burritos.
Great food! Just as good as the first location but with burritos. Fantastic food and chill atmosphere. Definitely coming back

Best sushi burrito I've had in Chicago, at a really afforable price. Korean-inspired Bulgogi wings or Pajeon are served piping hot and crispy. Will come back next time I'm in Wicker for something that's affordable and delicious. Give them your business🌊
Great food

Delicious! Prompt, friendly service. The food came out quickly. My friends got the sushi burritos, which they said were tasty and extremely filling. I got the kim-duk-man (kimbap/sushi, dukbokki/spicy rice cake and fish balls, and mandu/fried dumplings). The kim-duk-man was also extremely filling - the mandus and kimbaps were tasty but nothing exceptional, the dukbokki was my favorite and spicier than I expected. We also got the yuzu tea and job's tears tea. They were both good, but on the sweeter side. I added a whole cup of water to my tea after I finished and it was still good.
Great place! Had the miso soup and the Bibimbap for $10.00. Delicious!!

Great place for Korean food! I came here on a Friday night and loved everything first the cozy place and nice lights and music! Set the mood :) my bf was craving wings so we order one (10$ 10 wings), also we ordered the kimchi fries ($6) and de beef in the pan($11)! Everything was delicious and it was too much food for just 2, the beef plate is good enough for 2 with an appetizer. They also served us miso soup when we arrived and it was the best ever, it was just broth and green onions but it was delicious!!!
If you get a hot plate. You can share with another person. Serving size is large. Place is nice and easy. Great Korean food
Good all around. Pretty standard Korean food with a twist.
All items here always taste super fresh

Ordered take out a few days ago & got the vegetarian (also vegan) sushi burrito. Phenomenal. Sushi has always been a weakness, but I don't miss the fish at all. The tempura sweet potato was still slightly crunchy 10 min after when I got to take a bite & the sesame oil seasoned rice was amazing.
Awesome cheap food. Great Sushi Burritos and amazing chicken wings. Definitely worth going to. Very different from En Hakkore in bucktown, both great.
Great food. Sushi Burrito is amazing!

Fun and interesting food. Not too much variety in the format, mostly just sushi burritos, but there is variety in the fillings - from bebimbop to soft shell crab, everything was tasty, fresh, and creative.
great sushi burritos!
Good eats.
AWESOME sushi burritos 🍣 🌯✨
Sushi burrito. It's not a gimmick
Fresh, fast and super tasty!

I never knew I liked sushi burritos before. I didn't even know they existed. I just had the Fire burrito and it was wonderfully delicious. Pleasantly spicy. excellent mix of flavors. Absolutely worth trying.

The sushi burrito at En Hakkore 2.0 is fantastic. I got the Fire, which had a decent amount of heat. The burrito was stuffed full and yet did not fall apart when I unwrapped it little-by-little. The fish was delicate and had a nice color while the vegetables had a nice crunch to contrast.  The location is very good, relatively close to the Damen Blue Line station. In addition, there are not a lot of sushi-type places nearby and definitely not many sushi burrito places.  The layout and decor of the space is great as well - gentle lighting and charming, warm colors, setting up a cost atmosphere.  They do have disposable chopsticks at the tables, where I would have preferred reusable ones.  Overall, this is a wonderful place to have a quick bite.
Different vibe than the original on Damen.  Just as good. Tuna Poke' Salad is Bae. Don't walk by without checking it out.
